title: Blower system
description: Craig Mountain Lumber Co. Winchester, Idaho per Hayes and Company. This blueprint details a ventilation system designed to remove shavings and sawdust from the machine bays and pipe the excess debris to a shaving vault at least 300 feet away. The off-site location of the shaving vault was an insurance requirement with the intent of fire prevention. Due to this, a conveyor from the shaving vault was built to transport the shavings for use as  fuel to the furnaces and boilers of the mill. This image also depicts the configuration of mill machinery on the floor.
company names: Craig Mountain Lumber Company; Hayes. and Company
subject: blueprints; floor plans; ventilation systems; blowers; vaults; mills; saw mills; steam plants;

title: Map showing located line of Craig Mountain Railroad in Sec. 6-T.33N.-R.2W.B.M.
description: Map showing located line of Craig Mountain Railroad in Sec. 6-T.33N.-R.2W.B.M. A notarized affidavit attesting the accuracy of the cartography is signed by both J.J. McCreedy, the surveying engineer, and the President of Craig Mountain Lumber Company. These affidavits indicate that a copy of this map was submitted to the Secretary of the Interior "in order that the company may obtain the benefits of the act of Congress approved March 2, 1899, entitled "An Act to Provide for the Acquiring of Rights of Way by Railroad Companies through Indian Reservations; Indian Lands, and Indian Allotments and for other Purposes." This copy of the map has not been approved by the Department of the interior. It is possible that this copy was kept in the company records as a reference.
